  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting communities in processes of resistance in defence of water and territory</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the community of La Esmeralda there is lack of water and contamination of water sources in addition to other environmental damage due to exploitation and exploration of oil in a context of grave human rights violations in the context of ongoing armed conflict. This project seeks to the accompaniment and comprehensive advice to the women of the community of La Esmeralda, Acac&#xED;as, Meta, in their struggle for the defence of water and territory, through legal actions and strategic litigation; advocacy and communications; and training and strengthening of organisational processes, in order to advance in the effective guarantee of their rights and the protection and conservation of the piedemonte llanero, a region in Colombia between the Andes and the eastern plains. The water sources in this region have an impact on the Amazon.</narrative>
  </description>
